name: Akira
description: Red IPA rich in tropical fruit and mango aromas. Tropical wave goes towards well liked American Hops, giving it a sweet and bitter sensation.

name: Milfshake 2
description: A sour beer with a primary strawberry note supported by sour cherry, raspberry and vanilla. The full body of the beer will create the effect of eating a fruit cake. The product contains lactose

name: Salto Stout
description: Expect a burst of subtle milk chocolate, hazelnut and coffee flavours which melt away into a smooth and long lasting aftertaste.

name: Coco Taino
description: White IPA with Coconut and Vanilla is inspired by the Taino Indians, who made coconut a large part of their diet.

name: Hoptopod
description: Hoptopod is a real hoppy monster which was brought up in fermenter for five weeks.

name: 1019 IS NOW DOLCITA
description: This juicy pale ale is a younger brother of Dogma's 1019 NEIPA. What do you think? True or false?

name: Hedon IPA
description: IPA carefully crafted to provide the perfect balance between rich malt notes and an intense, refreshing hop aroma.

name: Andechser Hell
description: Clean tasting with a great malt profile. A pleasant sweetness and gentle carbonation.

name: Ernest
description: Ernest Bošnjak is the first Yugoslav director, cinematographer, producer and one of the founders of our cinematography who is known for his openness to new ideas, ventures, and we will assume also tastes!

name: Red & Black Currant Berliner Weisse
description: Arpus Brewing has created a great fruity experience with this new Berliner Weiße. The sour beer was brewed with red and black currants.

name: Noa Pecan Mud Cake Stout
description: Thick, rich and excessively decadent, this beer aims to bring back childhood memories.

name: Omnipollos Hatt IPA
description: IPA with Nelson, Motueka and Citra

name: Zodiak
description: Blend of grains, untouched post fermentation and aspiringly hopped with Simcoe, Citra and Centennial.

name: Cranberry Fudgesicle
description: This one is filled with toffee and cranberries for the perfect balance of sweet and sour. Think liquid toffee pudding mixed with freshly squeezed grandma’s cranberry juice.
